What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Physical Identity and Access Management Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Physical identity and access management market will reach at an estimated value of USD 1,596.92 million and grow at a CAGR of 14.10% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Rising future-proofing security operations is an essential factor driving the physical identity and access management market.

Physical identity and access management solutions offers a comprehensive management platform for the authentication and access of visitors, employees, contractors, and partners to organizational infrastructure. These systems help in providing a single point of control and also offer a completely efficient management and automated option to the corporate and industrial security landscape.

Rising stringent security compliances and government regulations is a crucial factor accelerating the market growth, also rising demand from organizations for diverse security systems to streamline security management of an entire organization or business, rising adoption of physical access control systems, growing awareness about data security across the emerging economies and rising government initiatives for standardizing security protocols are shifting from public sectors to private sectors are the major factors among others boosting the physical identity and access management market. Moreover, rising adoption of physical access control systems, rising need for business intelligence and increasing technological advancements and modernization in the management solutions will further create new opportunities for physical identity and access management market in the forecast period mentioned above.

However, rising lack of awareness about advanced security solutions among end users is the vital factor among others restraining the market growth, while rising remote identity proofing with the public, rising security breaches due to internal vulnerabilities and rising lack of skilled security analysts will further challenge the physical identity and access management market in the forecast period mentioned above.

